Applicant/Student (hereinafter referred to as "Student") has had the program fully and completely explained to him/her and agrees to abide by the terms listed in the Enrollment Agreement (hereinafter called "Agreement") and by regulations and policies of Campus University (hereinafter called "College"). This agreement and the catalog constitutes the entire agreement between the College and the Student. The Student understands that if the Agreement is accepted by the College it shall be deemed a binding contract. All signers have received and read a copy of the binding document and catalog.
I hereby enroll at Campus University for a program of study as indicated below, beginning:
This agreement is not contingent upon receiving financial aid or veterans' benefits. This College reserves the right to withhold the Degree, Diploma, Certificate or dismiss any student for maintaining poor academic standing, excessive absences, failure to comply with the regulations of the college as stated in current literature or for nonpayment of tuition and fees when due. Late charges of five (5%) percent or five dollars (whichever is less) will be added to any bill ten (10) days overdue. The Student will be liable for all late charges, reasonable attorney's fees, and all other costs and charges necessary for the collection of all unpaid fees.
